"title": "6260: uncircumcised",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6260",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Those who are outside the covenant of God.</p>\n<h2>Circumcision marked the covenant people of God</h2>\n<h3>God's covenant with Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:10-Gen17:12\">GEN 17:10–17:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:14\">GEN 17:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:6-Josh5:7\">JOS 5:6–5:7</a></p>\n<h3>Uncircumcised aliens participating in Jewish religious practices had first to be circumcised</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:48\">EXO 12:48</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:6-Ezek44:7\">EZK 44:6–44:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:9\">EZK 44:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:3\">ACT 11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:21\">ACT 21:21</a></p>\n<h2>The term ``uncircumcised''</h2>\n<h3>Used to describe Gentiles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:3\">JDG 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:18\">JDG 15:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:20\">2SA 1:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:10\">EZK 28:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek31:18\">EZK 31:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek32:19\">EZK 32:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek32:21\">EZK 32:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek32:24-Ezek32:32\">EZK 32:24–32:32</a></p>\n<h3>As a term of derision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:1\">ISA 52:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:14\">GEN 34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:6\">1SA 14:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:26\">1SA 17:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:36\">1SA 17:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:4\">1SA 31:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:4\">1CH 10:4</a></p>\n<h2>Uncircumcision represents a wrong inner spiritual attitude</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:25-Jer9:26\">JER 9:25–9:26</a></strong> <em>The tribes mentioned also practised male circumcision.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:51\">ACT 7:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:25-Rom2:27\">ROM 2:25–2:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:29-Rom3:30\">ROM 3:29–3:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:18-1Cor7:19\">1CO 7:18–7:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:6\">GAL 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:15\">GAL 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13\">COL 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>In Christ the barrier between the circumcised and uncircumcised is overcome</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:11-Eph2:13\">EPH 2:11–2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:9-Rom4:12\">ROM 4:9–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:13\">1CO 12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:11\">COL 3:11</a></p>",
